<button data-psycho-tab="phantom">Phantom Center</button>
</div>
<!-- HAAS -->
<div class="tab-content active" id="psycho-haas">
<div class="two-col">
<div>
<div class="canvas-wrap"><canvas height="200" id="haas-canvas" style="width:100%;height:200px" width="400"></canvas></div>
<div class="ctrl-group" style="margin-top:.8rem">
<div class="ctrl-label">Delay: <span id="haas-delay-val">15</span> ms</div>
<input id="haas-delay" max="50" min="0" style="width:100%" type="range" value="15"/>
</div>
</div>
<div class="info-card">
<h4>Haas Effect</h4>
<p style="font-size:.75rem;color:var(--dim);line-height:1.6">With delays of 1–30ms, the auditory system fuses the direct and delayed sounds, perceiving one sound located at the first-arrival source. Beyond 30–40ms the delay becomes an echo.</p>
<div style="margin-top:.8rem;font-size:.75rem">
<div id="haas-zone" style="color:var(--accent2)">● Fusion zone — perceived as one sound</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<!-- PRECEDENCE -->
<div class="tab-content" id="psycho-precedence">
<div class="two-col">
<div>
<div class="canvas-wrap"><canvas height="200" id="prec-canvas" style="width:100%;height:200px" width="400"></canvas></div>
<div class="ctrl-group" style="margin-top:.8rem">
<div class="ctrl-label">Level difference: <span id="prec-level-val">+6</span> dB (delayed louder)</div>
<input id="prec-level" max="20" min="0" style="width:100%" type="range" value="6"/>
</div>
</div>
<div class="info-card">
<h4>Precedence Effect</h4>
<p style="font-size:.75rem;color:var(--dim);line-height:1.6">The first-arriving sound determines perceived direction even when the delayed copy is up to ~10dB louder. This is the basis of concert hall design — early reflections enhance the direct sound.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<!-- COCKTAIL PARTY -->
<div class="tab-content" id="psycho-cocktail">
<div class="two-col">
<div>
<div class="canvas-wrap"><canvas height="220" id="cocktail-canvas" style="width:100%;height:220px" width="400"></canvas></div>
<div class="ctrl-group" style="margin-top:.8rem">
<div class="ctrl-label">Attention focus: <span id="cocktail-focus-val">Source A</span></div>
<input id="cocktail-focus" max="4" min="0" step="1" style="width:100%" type="range" value="0"/>
</div>
</div>
<div class="info-card">
<h4>Cocktail Party Effect</h4>
<p style="font-size:.75rem;color:var(--dim);line-height:1.6">The auditory system selectively attends to one conversation in a noisy environment using spatial, pitch, and timbre cues. Focused streams are perceptually enhanced; others are suppressed.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<!-- PHANTOM CENTER -->
<div class="tab-content" id="psycho-phantom">
<div class="two-col">
<div>
<div class="canvas-wrap"><canvas height="200" id="phantom-canvas" style="width:100%;height:200px" width="400"></canvas></div>
<div class="ctrl-group" style="margin-top:.8rem">
<div class="ctrl-label">Pan: <span id="phantom-pan-val">Center</span></div>
<input id="phantom-pan" max="100" min="-100" style="width:100%" type="range" value="0"/>
</div>
</div>
<div class="info-card">
<h4>Phantom Center Image</h4>
<p style="font-size:.75rem;color:var(--dim);line-height:1.6">Equal energy in both speakers creates a phantom center image — a perceptual illusion of a sound between the speakers. ILD controlled by pan law determines the perceived position.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>
